Do not fuse expression kernels into convolutions as custom activations.

The CHW SQ8 depthwise-conv kernel set has no KOP_CUSTOM variant, so any
MBv3-style graph (h-swish on a DW conv) dies in GenTile with "Can't find a
matching Convolution basic kernel" (CP 10.1, S75). Standalone expression
kernels always generate; convs keep their standard activation fusions.
Uniform standalone expressions are also the fairer latency-oracle shape:
every candidate arch pays activation cost through the same kernel path.

--- a/tools/nntool/nntool/graph/matches/matchers/fuse_gap_convs.py
+++ b/tools/nntool/nntool/graph/matches/matchers/fuse_gap_convs.py
@@ -43,8 +43,7 @@ VALID_ACTIVATIONS_SQ8 = (
     SigmoidNode,
     TanHNode,
-    HTanHNode,
-    ExpressionFusionNode
+    HTanHNode
 )
 
 VALID_FUSIONS_SQ8 = (
